--- title: "STAC Tutorial" description: "Learn how to use the GRASS addon t.stac to search and import STAC API data into a GRASS project." image: images/stac-to-the-future.png author: Corey T. White date: '2025-03-01' categories: [stac, grass-addon, tutorial] date-modified: today page-layout: full title-block-banner: true draft: false format: html: toc: true toc-depth: 4 tabsets: true code-copy: true code-fold: false code-tools: true mermaid: theme: forest other-links: - text: grass href: https://grass.osgeo.org - text: STAC href: https://stacspec.org/en lightbox: true canonical-url: true notebook-links: true jupyter: python3 execute: enabled: true keep-ipynb: true eval: false freeze: auto cache: true --- In this tutorial we will learn about the [t.stac](https://grass.osgeo.org/grass-stable/manuals/addons/t.stac.html) suite of tools for [GRASS](https://grass.osgeo.org). * [t.stac.catalog](https://grass.osgeo.org/grass-stable/manuals/addons/t.stac.catalog.html) - is a tool for exploring SpatioTemporal Asset Catalogs metadata from a STAC API. * [t.stac.collection](https://grass.osgeo.org/grass-stable/manuals/addons/t.stac.collection.html) - is a tool for exploring SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog (STAC) collection metadata. * [t.stac.item](https://grass.osgeo.org/grass-stable/manuals/addons/t.stac.item.html) - is a tool for exploring and importing SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog item metadata and assets into GRASS. ## Introduction SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog (STAC)... The tutorial assumes you already have GRASS installed on your machine. If not please [download and install GRASS](https://grass.osgeo.org/download/) before continuing the tutorial. ## Getting Started ### Start GRASS Session ::: {#config-grass .cell execution_count=1} ``` {.python .cell-code} # Import standard python packages import sys import subprocess from IPython.display import display, JSON, HTML import json import pandas as pd from pathlib import Path import seaborn as sns # import polars as pl # Ask GRASS where its Python packages are and add them to the path sys.path.append( subprocess.check_output(["grass", "--config", "python_path"], text=True).strip() ) # Import the GRASS python packages we need import grass.script as gs import grass.jupyter as gj ``` ::: Create a GRASS project ::: {#create-project .cell execution_count=2} ``` {.python .cell-code} gs.create_project("stac", epsg="32119", overwrite=True) ``` ::: and start a GRASS session ::: {#start-grass-session .cell execution_count=3} ``` {.python .cell-code} session = gj.init("stac") ``` ::: ### Install Addon The [t.stac](https://grass.osgeo.org/grass-stable/manuals/addons/t.stac.html) addons require the following Python packages. * [pystac (>=1.12)](https://pystac.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation.html) * [pystac_client (>=0.8)](https://pystac-client.readthedocs.io/en/stable/) * [tqdm (>=4.67)](https://tqdm.github.io/) You can install them using pip or the Python package manager of your choice. ```bash pip install pystac pystac_client tqdm ``` Now you can install the *t.stac* extensions. ::: {#install-t-stac .cell execution_count=4} ``` {.python .cell-code} gs.run_command("g.extension", extension="t.stac") ``` ::: ## Set computational region ::: {#grass-set-region .cell execution_count=5} ``` {.python .cell-code} gs.run_command( "g.region", n=236687, s=210391, e=616042, w=598921, nsres=10, ewres=10, flags="pa" ) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` projection: 99 (NAD83 / North Carolina) zone: 0 datum: nad83 ellipsoid: grs80 north: 236690 south: 210390 west: 598920 east: 616050 nsres: 10 ewres: 10 rows: 2630 cols: 1713 cells: 4505190 ``` ::: ::: ::: {#cell-display-interactive-region .cell execution_count=6} ``` {.python .cell-code} m = gj.InteractiveMap(use_region=True) m.save(filename="outputs/basic_map.html") display(m.show()) ``` ::: {#display-interactive-region .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: ## STAC API ::: {#set-stac-catalog-url .cell execution_count=7} ``` {.python .cell-code} stac_url = "https://earth-search.aws.element84.com/v1/" ``` ::: ### Searching STAC Catalogs ::: {.panel-tabset} ## Python ::: {#tbl-stac-catalog .cell execution_count=8} ``` {.python .cell-code} catalogs_json = gs.parse_command( "t.stac.catalog", url=stac_url, flags="b", format="json" ) df_catalogs = pd.json_normalize(catalogs_json) display(df_catalogs.T.head(10)) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: #### View the items with iPyleaflet ::: {#5b35b895 .cell execution_count=22} ``` {.python .cell-code} import random m = gj.InteractiveMap(use_region=False) m.add_vector( "sentinel_2_items", style={"opacity": 1, "dashArray": "9", "fillOpacity": 0.1, "weight": 1}, hover_style={"color": "white", "dashArray": "0", "fillOpacity": 0.5}, style_callback=lambda f: { "color": "black", "fillColor": random.choice(["red", "yellow", "green", "orange"]), } ) display(m.show()) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: ### Download and Import Rasters ### Register STRDS ::: {.panel-tabset} ## Python ::: {#tbl-collection-items-assets .cell tbl-cap='Sentinel 2 Items Assets Metadata' execution_count=23} ``` {.python .cell-code} import grass.script as gs import grass.jupyter as gj stac_query = {"eo:cloud_cover": {"lt": 10}} items_assets_json = gs.parse_command( "t.stac.item", url=stac_url, collection_id="sentinel-2-l2a", datetime="2024-04-01/2024-09-30", asset_keys="red,nir", format="json", query=json.dumps(stac_query) ) ``` ::: ## Terminal ::: {#tbl-collection-items-assets-terminal .cell tbl-cap='Sentinel 2 Items Assets Metadata' execution_count=24} ``` {.python .cell-code} !t.stac.item url="https://earth-search.aws.element84.com/v1/" collection_id="sentinel-2-l2a" datetime="2024-04-01/2024-09-30" asset_keys="red,nir" format="json" query='{"eo:cloud_cover": {"lt": 10}}' ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` WARNING: Flag 'j' is deprecated and will be removed in a future release. Create the space time dataset gs.run_command( "t.create", output="sentinel_2", type="strds", temporaltype="absolute", title="Sentinel 2 Red/NIR Bands", description="Sentinel 2 Red/NIR Bands from 2024-04-01/2024-09-30", overwrite=True, ) ``` ::: Download the data ::: {#download-assets .cell execution_count=30} ``` {.python .cell-code} print(gs.run_command( "t.stac.item", url=stac_url, collection_id="sentinel-2-l2a", datetime="2024-04-01/2024-09-30", asset_keys="red,nir", query=json.dumps(stac_query), strds_output="outputs/s2_red_nir.txt", format="json", method="nearest", resolution="value", resolution_value="10", extent="region", nprocs=7, memory=1024 * 7, flags="d", )) ``` ::: Register the data ::: {#register-strds .cell execution_count=31} ``` {.python .cell-code} # Register the output maps into a space time dataset gs.run_command( "t.register", input="sentinel_2", file="outputs/s2_red_nir.txt", type="raster" ) ``` ::: ::: {#db27602b .cell execution_count=32} ``` {.python .cell-code} gs.run_command("t.info", type="strds", input="sentinel_2") ``` ::: ::: {#cell-display-composite .cell execution_count=33} ``` {.python .cell-code} m = gj.Map(use_region=True) m.d_rgb( red="sentinel-2-l2a.S2A_17SPV_20240909_0_L2A.red", blue="sentinel-2-l2a.S2A_17SPV_20240909_0_L2A.nir", green="sentinel-2-l2a.S2A_17SPV_20240909_0_L2A.nir", ) m.d_barscale() m.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-composite-output-1.png){#display-composite} ::: ::: #### Calculate NDVI ::: {#deb821df .cell execution_count=34} ``` {.python .cell-code} gs.run_command( "t.rast.mapcalc", inputs=["sentinel_2.nir", "sentinel_2.red"], output="ndvi", basename="ndvi", method="follows", expression=( "float(if('sentinel_2.nir' >= 10000.0, 10000.0, 'sentinel_2.nir') - if('sentinel_2.red' >= 10000.0, 10000.0, 'sentinel_2.red')) / (if('sentinel_2.nir' >= 10000.0, 10000.0, 'sentinel_2.nir') + if('sentinel_2.red' >= 10000.0, 10000.0, 'sentinel_2.red'))" ), overwrite=True, flags="n", ) ``` ::: ::: {#49bbbe4b .cell execution_count=35} ``` {.python .cell-code} gs.run_command("t.list", type="strds") ``` ::: Plot the NDVI ::: {#8917ced8 .cell execution_count=36} ``` {.python .cell-code} strds_df = pd.DataFrame( gs.parse_command( "t.rast.list", input="ndvi", order="start_time", columns=["name", "semantic_label", "start_time", "end_time", "min", "max"], format="csv", ) ) # Convert start_time to datetime for better formatting strds_df["start_time"] = pd.to_datetime(strds_df["start_time"]) sns.lineplot( x="start_time", y="max", data=strds_df ) # Format x-axis labels for better readability import matplotlib.dates as mdates import matplotlib.pyplot as plt plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d')) plt.gcf().autofmt_xdate() # Auto-rotate date labels ``` ::: ::: {#ac450c8f .cell layout-ncol='3' execution_count=37} ``` {.python .cell-code} ndvi_list = gs.parse_command( "t.rast.list", input="ndvi", order="start_time", columns=["name", "semantic_label", "start_time", "end_time", "min", "max"], format="csv", ) gs.run_command("t.rast.colors", input="ndvi", color="ndvi") for ndvi in ndvi_list: map_name = ndvi.get("name") m = gj.Map(use_region=True, width=500) m.d_rast(map=map_name) m.d_barscale() m.d_legend(raster=map_name, flags="b") m.show() ``` ::: ::: {#cell-display-time-series .cell execution_count=38} ``` {.python .cell-code} ndvi_rasters = [ i.get("name") for i in gs.parse_command( "t.rast.list", input="ndvi", order="start_time", columns=["name"], format="csv", ) ] # Create Time Series Map m = gj.SeriesMap(use_region=True) m.add_rasters( rasters=ndvi_rasters ) m.d_barscale() m.render() m.show() ``` ::: {#display-time-series .cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=231} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: ::: {#cell-display-ndvi-maps .cell layout-ncol='3' execution_count=39} ``` {.python .cell-code} import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec from PIL import Image def generate_map(map_name): m = gj.Map(use_region=True) m.d_rast(map=map_name) m.d_legend(raster=map_name, flags="b") m.d_barscale() return m for raster in ndvi_rasters: ndvi_map = generate_map(raster) ndvi_map.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 1](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-1.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 2](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-2.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 3](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-3.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 4](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-4.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 5](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-5.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 6](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-6.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Day 7](t_stac_tutorial_files/figure-html/display-ndvi-maps-output-7.png){#display-ndvi-maps} ::: ::: ## References - [pystac Documentation](https://pystac.readthedocs.io/) - [pystac_client Documentation](https://pystac-client.readthedocs.io/)
